verbose_text: As expected, we found elevated levels of CCL3, CCL4, and CCL5, particularly in 10-month and 15-month-old APPPS1 mice (15-month-old, CCL3 : 14.3 +/- 1.6 pg/mg, CCL4 : 2.1 +/- 0.1 pg/mg and CCL5 : 1.8 +/- 0.1 pg/mg, n = 11; P < 0.001) vs. WT mice (15-month-old, CCL3 : 1.0 +/- 0.1 pg/mg, CCL4 : 0.4 +/- 0.1 pg/mg and CCL5 : 1.2 +/- 0.1 pg/mg, n = 8; Fig. XREF_FIG).
